# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-roadmap

Model/effort: Sonnet / medium.

Keeps the plan aligned with reality. Compares the stated roadmap and backlog against
shipped work, then corrects the plan so it reflects what is done, in flight, and next.

## Steps
1. OPEN-lite: fetch and prune; read the latest `05-logs/` entry, the master index, and
   the current roadmap; state the reconciliation objective.
2. Survey what shipped: merged PRs, closed issues, and new capabilities since the last
   reconciliation.
3. Diff shipped work against the roadmap and backlog; identify done, drifted, stale, and
   missing items.
4. Update the roadmap and backlog: close completed items, re-prioritize, and add newly
   discovered work as issues.
5. CLOSE-lite: append a continuity entry summarizing the reconciliation; update the
   decision board if priorities shifted; push.

## Done when
The roadmap and backlog match shipped reality, new work is captured as issues, and the
reconciliation is logged and pushed.
